(44, 21, 1, 9, 20, 41, 42, NULL, 'Departure and Farewell Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of departure and farewell in both passages. In Acts, the journey begins after a farewell, while in 1 Samuel, David and Jonathan part ways with a solemn promise.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 1, 42, 8, 22, 22, 'and had launched', 'Journey by Sea', 'Both passages emphasize the act of launching forth from one location to another by ship. This connection highlights the theme of travel and movement across water in the ministry of Jesus and the apostles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 1, 44, 16, 10, 11, 'with a straight course', 'Journeying with a Straight Course', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''with a straight course,'' highlighting the directness of the journeys undertaken by Paul and his companions. This connection illustrates the urgency and purposefulness of their missionary efforts.', 'keyword', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 1, 44, 20, 37, 38, 'after we were gotten from them', 'Departure and Farewell', 'Both passages emphasize the emotional farewell between Paul and his companions as he departs on a journey. Acts 20:37-38 describes their sorrowful goodbye, while Acts 21:1 recounts the actual departure from them.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 2, 32, 1, 3, 3, NULL, 'Journey by Ship', 'Both passages emphasize the act of finding a ship to embark on a journey. In Acts, the ship is headed to Phenicia, while in Jonah, it is going to Tarshish, illustrating a common theme of maritime travel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 2, 44, 11, 19, 19, 'Phenicia', 'Connection through Geographic Reference', 'Both passages emphasize the location of Phenicia, linking the travels of Paul in Acts 21:2 with the earlier scattering of believers in Acts 11:19. This connection highlights the significance of Phenicia as a place of ministry and movement in the early church.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 2, 44, 15, 3, 3, 'Phenicia', 'Journey Through Phenicia', 'Both passages emphasize travel through Phenicia, highlighting its significance in the journeys of the early church. Acts 15:3 mentions passing through Phenice, while Acts 21:2 describes boarding a ship sailing to Phenicia.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 2, 44, 27, 6, 6, 'ship sailing', 'Connection of Ship Journeys', 'Both passages emphasize the act of boarding a ship for travel. The mention of ships in both contexts highlights the theme of maritime journeys in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 3, 40, 4, 24, 24, 'Syria', 'Connection through Geographic Reference', 'Both passages emphasize the region of Syria, linking the travels of Paul in Acts to the healing ministry of Jesus in Matthew. This connection highlights the significance of Syria as a place of healing and ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 3, 44, 4, 36, 36, 'Cyprus', 'Connection through Cyprus', 'Both passages emphasize Cyprus as a significant location. Acts 21:3 mentions Cyprus in the context of a journey, while Acts 4:36 identifies Barnabas as being from Cyprus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 3, 44, 12, 20, 20, 'Tyre', 'Connection through Tyre', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Tyre. In Acts 21:3, Tyre is a location of arrival, while in Acts 12:20, it is a place of political interaction and dependence on Herod.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 3, 7, 10, 6, 6, 'Syria', 'Connection of Locations and Idolatry', 'This connection highlights the geographical link between Tyre, a city mentioned in Acts, and the gods of Syria referenced in Judges. Both passages emphasize the influence of surrounding nations on Israel''s faithfulness to God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 3, 10, 8, 6, 6, 'Syria', 'Connection Between Syria References', 'Both passages emphasize Syria''s significance in biblical narratives. Acts mentions sailing into Syria, while 2 Samuel discusses David''s military actions in Syria, highlighting its importance in the region.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 3, 19, 45, 12, 12, 'Tyre', 'Connection between Tyre references', 'Both passages emphasize Tyre as a significant location. Acts mentions landing at Tyre, while Psalms refers to the daughter of Tyre bringing gifts, highlighting its importance in trade and favor.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 3, 19, 87, 4, 4, 'Tyre', 'Connection Between Tyre in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize Tyre as a significant location. In Acts, Tyre is mentioned as a landing point, while in Psalms, it is noted among other cities of importance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 4, 44, 20, 22, 23, 'that he should not go up to Jerusalem', 'Connection of Paul''s Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s journey to Jerusalem and the warnings he receives about impending hardships. In Acts 21:4, disciples warn Paul through the Spirit, while in Acts 20:22-23, Paul acknowledges the Holy Ghost''s warnings of bonds and afflictions awaiting him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 4, 44, 21, 10, 12, 'that he should not go up to Jerusalem', 'Warnings Against Going to Jerusalem', 'This connection highlights the warnings given to Paul about going to Jerusalem. Both passages emphasize the guidance through the Spirit and the prophetic message regarding the dangers he would face.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 4, 40, 10, 11, 11, NULL, 'Travel Instructions for Disciples', 'This connection highlights the theme of guidance for disciples in their travels. Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking direction and staying in a place until further instructions are received.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 4, 55, 1, 17, 17, NULL, 'Seeking and Finding Connections', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking out individuals for support and guidance. In Acts, disciples advise Paul not to go to Jerusalem, while in 2 Timothy, he is sought out diligently, indicating the importance of relationships in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
